==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tonsil
<hw>Ton"sil</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tonsill</ets><?/, pl.: cf. F. <ets>tonsille</ets>. ]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the two glandular organs situated in the
throat at the sides of the fauces. The tonsils are sometimes called the
<altname>almonds</altname>, from their shape.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

